Политики осваивают Internet...
  Conservatives have latched onto computer networking as a means of
  communicating their message and maintaining cohesion. Although the
  Democratic party started using a computer forum to dispense information
  before the GOP did, a democratic activist asserts that conservatives are
  "definitely" ahead of liberal groups on using the mechanism effectively.
  (Wall Street Journal 3/16/94 A1)


Микрософт пытается проникнуть на рынок Internet, спутникового и цифрово-
го кабельного телевидения...

  Фирма Tele-Communications Inc. и Microsoft будут совместно тестировать
  систему  интерактивного  кабельного  телевидения  в  Сиэтле и Денвере.
  Microsoft обеспечит доработки Windows NT позволяющие использовать ее в
  качестве сервера для кабельных сетей.

  McCAW & GATES PLAN SATELLITE NETWORK
  Two high-tech entrepreneurs are planning a $9 billion wireless "global
  Internet," using low earth orbit satellites to provide a wide array of
  wireless interactive voice, data and video services. Craig McCaw, McCaw
  Cellular Communications, and Bill Gates, Microsoft, envision a system that
  employs 840 refrigerator-sized satellites operating the 30/20 Ghz Ka-band
  to connect handheld phones and other electronic devices to telephone
  networks around the world. As currently planned, the Teledesic Corp.
  project is more than 10 times the size of Motorola's low earth orbit
  Iridium project. (Wall Street Journal 3/21/94 A3)

  MICROSOFT PLANS ANOTHER DATA NETWORK
  Microsoft is teaming up with Mobile Telecommunications Technologies Corp.
  (Mtel), the nation's largest paging company, to build a $150 million
  wireless data network. The Nationwide Wireless Network will offer two-way
  data messaging for users of laptops, alphanumeric pagers and a new general
  of Mtel-developed pocket communicators. (Wall Street Journal 3/24/94 B6)
 #

