Не стоит подглядывать в чужие электронные ящики...
  The Dallas Morning News says three U.S. reporters
  have been reported to the U.S. Olympic Committee for allegedly breaking
  into Tonya Harding's private electronic mailbox. The reporters were
  observed Tuesday morning reading what appeared to be a directory of
  messages sent to the figure skater through the Olympic Info '94 network.
